# Belt-and-suspenders. The allowlist Dockerfile is the load-bearing control
# (it COPYs explicit paths, never `.`), but this keeps the build context
# minimal and is a second line of defense against accidental disclosure.
#
# Two images build from this same root context:
#   - the static host (`Dockerfile`)        -> context/ issuer/ badges/ nginx/ README.md
#   - the on-demand render (`service/Dockerfile`) -> service/ generator/ badges/
# so service/ and generator/ are re-included for the render build. Both are
# public source; each Dockerfile still COPYs only its explicit paths.
*
!context/
!context/**
!issuer/
!issuer/**
!badges/
!badges/**
!README.md
!nginx/
!nginx/**
!service/
!service/**
!generator/
!generator/**
